1. Wrap npm run start:all in a shell script
    Create a startup script:
        nano /home/administrator/ITS/start-all.sh

    Paste this inside start-all.sh :
        #!/bin/bash
        cd /home/administrator/ITS/FRONTEND
        npm run start:all

    Make it executable:
        chmod +x /home/administrator/ITS/start-all.sh

2. Create a Systemd Service:
    sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/start-all.service

    Paste the following configuration inside start-all.service:

    [Unit]
    Description=Start Angular and ASP.NET Core Project
    After=network.target

    [Service]
    Type=simple
    WorkingDirectory=/home/administrator/ITS
    ExecStart=/home/administrator/ITS/start-all.sh
    Restart=always
    RestartSec=10
    User=administrator
    Environment=PATH=/usr/bin:/usr/local/bin
    Environment=NODE_ENV=production

    [Install]
    WantedBy=multi-user.target


3. Enable and Start the Service: 
    sudo systemctl daemon-reload
    sudo systemctl enable start-all
    sudo systemctl start start-all



    sudo systemctl disable start-all
    sudo systemctl stop start-all


4. Check if it's Running:
    sudo systemctl status start-all
    journalctl -u start-all -e



